### HTML

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Image Gallery</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>

    <div class="gallery">
        <div class="thumbnails">
          <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Thumbnail1" class="thumbnail">
          <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Thumbnail 2" class="thumbnail">
          <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="thumbnail 3" class="thumbnail">      
        </div>
        <div class="full-Image">
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Full Image" id="fullImage">
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="script.js"> </script>
    
</body>
</html>


```

### CSS

----------------

```css

.gallery {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}

.thumbnails {
  display: flex;
}

.thumbnail {
  margin-right: 10px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.full-Image {
  margin-top: 20px;
}

#fullImage {
  max-width: 100%;
  height: auto;
}
```


### JS
----------------


```javascript 

const thumbnails = document.querySelectorAll(".thumbnail");


// function to display full Image

function displyFullImage(event) {
    const fullImage = document.getElementById("fullImage");
    const thumbnailSrc = event.target.src.replace("-thumb", "");
    fullImage.src = thumbnailSrc;
}


// Add click event listeners to thumbnails
thumbnails.forEach(thumbnail => {
    thumbnail.addEventListener("click", displyFullImage);
});

```
